{"000-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme Guidelines & Complete Details"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Andhra Pradesh govt. issues AP YSR Rythu Bandhu Scheme guidelines for farmers, check details to avail assistance of Rs. 12,500 p.a, fill apply online form from 15 October 2019"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme Guidelines", "001-normal": "To avail assistance of Rs. 12,500 per year, farmer will have to follow the conditions mentioned in the YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme Guidelines. Under this scheme, there is no restriction on land holdings by land-owner families. However, the minimum area requirement which is to be taken on lease by a single individual landless tenant farmer is different:-", "002-listElement": "- 1 acre for agriculture, horticulture or sericulture.", "003-listElement": "- In case tenant farmer grows vegetables, flower & fodder crops, then minimum area is half acre.", "004-listElement": "- For beter vines, minimum area requirement is 0.1 acre.", "005-normal": "People must also check the list of exclusion categories so as to avail benefits of YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "Exclusion Categories of AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme", "001-normal": "Here are the complete details of exclusion categories for AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme. Any person in the following categories of higher economic status shall not be eligible for scheme benefits:-", "002-listElement": "- All institutional landholders, farmer\u2019s families in which 1 or more of its members are former or present holders of constitutional posts and former or present ministers & state ministers.", "003-listElement": "- Former or present Members of Lok Sabha / Rajya Sabha / State Legislative Assemblies / State Legislative Councils, former and present Mayors of Municipal Corporations, former and present chairpersons of district panchayats are not eligible.", "004-listElement": "- All serving or retired officers and employees of Central / State Government Ministries / Offices / Departments and their field units are not eligible.", "005-listElement": "- Central or State PSEs and attached offices / Autonomous Institutions under Government as well as regular employees of Local Bodies (excluding multi tasking staff / Class IV / Group D employees) are also not eligible.", "006-listElement": "- All superannuated / retired pensioners, whose monthly pension is Rs. 10,000 or more (excluding multi-tasking staff / Class IV / Group D employees) of the above category too are excluded.", "007-listElement": "- Persons who have paid income tax in the last assessment year as well as professionals such as doctors, engineers, lawyers, chartered accountants and architects registered with professional bodies and carrying out profession by undertaking practices are also not eligible.", "008-listElement": "- Persons who have paid commercial tax / professional tax / GST during the last assessment year, persons owning farmlands converted into house sites, aquaculture, or any other non-agriculture usage, either updated or not updated in the revenue records are also not eligible.", "009-normal": "Any person finding any difficulty regarding YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme in AP can dial toll free nubers 1100 or 1902 to raise grievance. Previous scheme of the TDP govt. namely Annadata Sukhibhava has been scrapped in which govt. announced to provide Rs. 15,000 per annum to farmers.", "010-normal": "The scheme would be implemented from 15 October 2019 & people can then fill [AP YSR Rythu Bandhu Scheme Apply Online Form](https://sarkariyojana.com/ysr-rythu-bharosa-scheme-andhra-pradesh/) after its official launch.", "011-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/govt-announces-rythu-bharosa-guidelines/article29462153.ece"}}